qx|B06,|ht|b|cs|1|cp|4|fp|1|at|^-{  4-Suit Jacoby Transfers - Transfer to Minors }
^-|fp||CP||CS||AT|^B@2
One variant of Jacoby that I use is 4-suit Jacoby transfer. A 2@S bid by responder is a transfer to clubs, and a 2NT bid is a transfer to diamonds. Since there are two bids between the transfer bid and the transfer suit, opener now has two choices. |
PG| ***** 19 ***** |


AT|

With good support (ONLY if you have 1 of the top 3 honors, regardless of the length of your support), opener "accepts" the transfer by not bidding the suit (1NT-2@S-2NT or 1NT-2NT-3@C). BTW, Notrumper alwyas has at least 2-card minor.|
PG| ***** 20 ***** |


AT| 
With less than good support, opener "rejects" the transfer by bidding the transfer suit (1NT-2@S-3@C or 1NT-2NT-3@D). |
PG| ***** 21 ***** |


AT|

This is somewhat counter-intuitive, as one would think the more natural way would be for opener to bid the suit to "accept" the transfer. However, the reason for doing it this way is that it is more likely that opener will end up as declarer.|
PG| ***** 22 ***** |


AT|

Again, this convention can be used for two purposes:
1. To allow responder to bid 3NT with a 6-8 point hand and a 6-card minor suit if opener accepts the transfer. Otherwise, the contract will be 3 of the minor.

2. To play in 3 of a minor with 5 or fewer points and a 6-card minor.|
PG| ***** 23 ***** |


AT|

As an important clarification. If you play 4-suit Jacoby transfer you cannot make a 2NT invitational bid. In another word, 1N-P-2N is not invitational bid. In its place you bid Stayman followed by 2NT. Now we have to 1NT bidder should be alert to the following:
^C1NT-2@C-2@S-2NT does not necessarily promise hearts and simply shows a 2N invite.
^C1NT-2@C-2@H-2N denies 4 spades by responder and simply shows a 2N invite. 
^B@2If responder bids Stayman with an invitational hand and 4 spades, he must bid 2@S when opener responds 2@H (e.g. the auction should go 1N-2@C-2@H-2@S).|
PG| ***** 24 ***** |


AT|

^B@2Let us look at a few examples illustrating 4-suit jacoby transfer. Your partnership is playing 4-way Jacoby transfer.|
PG| ***** 25 ***** |


